definition.value: An optically active form of averantin having S-configuration.
A tetrahydroxyanthraquinone that is 1,3,6,8-tetrahydroxy-9,10-anthraquinone bearing a 1,5-dihydroxyhexyl substituent at position 2 (the 1'S,5'S-diastereomer).
A hydroxyanthraquinone that is 1,3,6,8-tetrahydroxy-9,10-anthraquinone bearing a 1,5-dihydroxyhexyl substituent at position 2 (the 1'S,5'R-diastereomer).

An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is 3,4,5,6-tetrahydro-2H-2,6-epoxyanthra[2,3-b]oxocine-8,13-dione substituted at position 2 by a methyl group and at positions 7, 9 and 11 by hydroxy groups (the S,S-diastereomer)
A lipid A that is lipid A-core in which the anomeric phosphate is replaced by a diphosphate.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (8Z,11Z,14Z)-3-oxoicosa-8,11,14-trienoic acid.
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of isoheptadecanoic acid.
A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of (25S)-Delta(4)-dafachronic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of (25S)-Delta(7)-dafachronic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

Members of the class of tetrahydrochromenochromene that consists of a cis-fused tetrahydrochromeno[3,4-b]chromene skeleton and its substituted derivatives. The term was originally restricted to natural products, but is now also used to describe semi-synthetic and fully synthetic compounds.
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (E)-isopentadec-2-enoic acid.
An aromatic ketone that is norbornane with 2-endo-amino, 2-exo-benzoyl and 3-exo-phenyl substituents.
A cyclic hydrocarbon consisting of cyclohexane with a methylene bridge linking positions 1 and 4.
A eudesmane sesquiterpenoid that is octahydro-2H-3,9a-methano-1-benzoxepine substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 2, 5a and 9 (the 3R,5aS,9R,9aS stereoisomer).
Any sesquiterpenoid with a dihydroagarofuran skeleton.
A dicarboxylic acid monoester that is succinic acid monoesterified with 6-endo-amino-6-exo-benzoyl-5-exo-phenylnorbornan-2-ol
A cholestanoid that is 5alpha-cholest-7-ene substituted at position 3 by an oxo group.
An EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of ceramidase (EC 3.5.1.23).
alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-D-Manp in which the anomeric configuration at the reducing end is beta.
An amino disaccharide comprising a beta-D-mannose residue linked (1->4) to an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue at the reducing end.
A PPAR modulator which activates the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-gamma.
A Delta(7)-dafachronic acid that has S configuration at position 25 (the carbon attached to the carboxy group).
An amino disaccharide composed of N-acetylneuraminic acid and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked (2->6).

A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprised of a trisaccharide chain of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid, 6-O-sulfo-beta-D-glactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->4), to the GlcNAC residue of which is also linked (1->3) an alpha-L-fucose residue.
An oxazolidinone that is the N(6)-(4S)-4-[(1R)-1-hydroxyethyl]-5-oxo-1,3-oxazolidin-2-ylidene derivative of adenosine. Obtained by cyclocondensation of N(6)-threonylcarbamoyladenosine.
A Delta(4)-dafachronic acid that has S configuration at position 25 (the carbon attached to the carboxy group). Found in Caenorhabditis elegans.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprised of a trisaccharide chain of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->4), to the galactose residue of which is also linked (1->4) an N-acetyl-beta-L-galactosamine residue.
A branched amino trisaccharide in which two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl residues are linked (2->3) and (2->6) to an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of all-cis-8,11,14,17-icosatetraenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
An amino disaccharide comprised of an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl residue linked (2->3) to N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine
An amino trisaccharide comprised of alpha-neuraminic acid, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->4).
A precorrin containing seven C-methyl groups introduced into the tetrapyrrole framework.
A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of (25S)-cholestenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of (25S)-dafachronic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of (25R)-Delta(7)-dafachronic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid acid anion that is the conjugate base of (25R)-Delta(4)-dafachronic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A (2R)-2-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is (R)-lactic acid substituted at position 3 by a 3,4-dihydroxyphenyl group.
A UDP-3-O-[(3R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl]-D-glucosamine(1-) in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-3-oxoicosatetraenoic acid.
A triterpene that is docosahydropicene substituted by 8 methyl groups at positions 2, 2, 4a, 6a, 8a, 9, 12b and 14a.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is beta-amyrin carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at position 30 as well as an oxo group at position 11.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is beta-amyrin carrying two oxo substituents at positions 11 and 30.
A cyclic purine dinucleotide that is the 3',5'-cyclic dimer of AMP.
A benzoate that is the conjugate base of methyl red, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A cyclic purine dinucleotide that consists of AMP and GMP units cyclised via 3',5'-linkages.
A 3beta-sterol that is 5alpha-cholest-8(14)-en-3beta-ol bearing an alpha-methyl substituent at position 4.
Any anthocyanidin cation having one or more glycosyl residues attached at unspecified positions.
An anthocyanin cation that is cyanidin(1+) carrying two beta-D-glucosyl residues at positions 3 and 7.
A linear amino trisaccharide comprising N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-6-O-sulfo-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->3).
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (3E,5Z)-tetradecadienoyl-CoA.
